    "Moodle workshops are a very basic peer-assessment tool, providing nothing more than a way for students and instructors to view the reviews done by student peers, and so are not AI assisted.",
    "Eighty percent reliability was found.",
    "Strategic behavior in peer assessment was considered by Stelmakh et al. (2021), especially when peers were in competition with each other.",
    "In the latter case, assessors might be incentivized to misreport evaluations in order to improve their own final standing.",
    "The authors offered a statistical model for identifying such outliers which had strong detection power."
